ducts positioning pricing and go-to-market strategies.&nbsp;Maintain a comprehensive database of competitive intelligence to inform decision-making.&nbsp;Product Positioning:&nbsp;Develop and refine product positioning strategies based on competitive insights.&nbsp;Differentiate our products in the market by highlighting key strengths and unique selling propositions.&nbsp;Go-to-Market Strategy:&nbsp;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to develop and execute effective go-to-market strategies.&nbsp;Ensure that go-to-market plans leverage competitive intelligence to maximize product success.&nbsp;Sales Enablement:&nbsp;Provide the sales team with up-to-date competitive insights and training materials.&nbsp;Equip the sales team with the knowledge and tools needed to effectively position our products against competitors.&nbsp;Market Trends and Industry Analysis:&nbsp;Stay abreast of industry trends technological advancements and regulatory changes.&nbsp;Analyze how these factors impact the competitive landscape and our product positioning.&nbsp;Content Development:&nbsp;Create compelling marketing content that effectively communicates our products advantages over competitors.&nbsp;Develop content that educates both internal teams and external audiences on competitive differentiators.&nbsp;Collaboration:&nbsp;Collaborate closely with product management marketing and sales teams to align strategies with overall business goals.&nbsp;Act as a key liaison between product management and other departments to ensure a unified approach.&nbsp;Measurement and Optimization:&nbsp;Establish key performance indicators (KPIs) to measure the success of competitive intelligence efforts.&nbsp;Continuously optimize strategies based on performance metrics and market feedback.&nbsp;Qualifications:&nbsp;Bachelors degree in marketing business or a related field; MBA is a plus.&nbsp;Proven experience in product marketing with a specific focus on competitive intelligence.&nbsp;Strong analytical and research skills.&nbsp;Excellent communication and presentation skills.&nbsp;Ability to translate complex competitive insights into actionable strategies.&nbsp;Demonstrated ability to work collaboratively in cross-functional teams.&nbsp;Results-oriented mindset with a focus on achieving competitive advantage.&nbsp;&nbsp;

$125000 - $130000 a year
